}}As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]]<ref name=":0" /> there were 973 people, 439 households, and 362 families residing in the village. The population density was {{Convert|865.66|PD/sqmi|PD/km2}}. There were 389 housing units at an average density of {{Convert|346.09|/sqmi|/km2}}. The racial makeup of the village was 90.24% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.00% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.62% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.21% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.10% [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 1.54% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 7.30% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 7.50% of the population.

There were 439 households, out of which 32.6% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 64.24% were married couples living together, 7.74% had a female householder with no husband present, and 17.54% were non-families. 15.95% of all households were made up of individuals, and 10.48% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 3.29 and the average family size was 3.02.

The village's age distribution consisted of 22.0% under the age of 18, 8.1% from 18 to 24, 23.1% from 25 to 44, 29.5% from 45 to 64, and 17.4% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 43.2 years. For every 100 females, there were 85.3 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 87.1 males.

The median income for a household in the village was $101,750, and the median income for a family was $112,794. Males had a median income of $53,942 versus $24,857 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the village was $36,725. About 2.5% of families and 8.6% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 12.2% of those under age 18 and 3.9% of those age 65 or over.{{clear left}}

